Quote:  The accompanying sauteed watercress and pikopiko were real enough, as was the bed of kumara mash studded with pieces of tawea - the correct name for the elongated cultivar of Maori potato known crudely as tuae kuri (and if you don't know the meaning of that, I'm not telling, except to say that kuri means dog).
