Vol / Page:  C4
Edition:
Quote:  A research project to re-establish taewa - Maori potatoes - as a sustainable commercial horticultural crop has received $100,000 from a new Technology New Zealand fund for Maori collectives. Taewa have been grown in New Zealand for centuries, forming the basis of the market garden industry established in the 1800s to supply early European settlers.
